contact.facebookName: Melt Café at Mandarin Oriental, Singapore

tip.text: Very disappointed with the quality of the food here. Really mediocre & not worth its pricetag. If you have to, try the chicken with ume and Shiso. Love its complex flavours and uplifting fragrance.
Sweet potato latte is everything I imagined it to be - earthy, comforting with a subtle sweetness. Love the house miso dressing on their Canvas Salad too. Blanc bacon pasta is also very yums.
Try their butter chicken, mutton biryani, fish tikka, and aloo padi. Garlic naans are so fluffy I could die. By far, everything I've tried here are delicious!
